<P>Major Labilliere had a pair of colours given him by the Devon&s;hire family in a very early year of his life, and bearing them one day in the field, when the wind was high, he fell with them. The Duche&s;s hearing of this circum&s;tance, ralli|ed the en&s;ign on the occa&s;ion, and a&s;ked him, what had he done, &s;uppo&s;ing they had blown away? when the young &s;oldier gallantly replied, "Then I &s;hould have followed them, plea&s;e your Grace."</P>
