<ITEM>29 Why is a red-hair'd lady like a band of &s;ol|diers?</ITEM>
<ITEM>Becau&s;e &s;he bears fire&punc;locks.</ITEM>
<ITEM>30 Why is a man on hor&s;eback like a fan?</ITEM>
<ITEM>Becau&s;e he is mounted.</ITEM>
<ITEM>31 Why is a ba$$el of beer, almo&s;t drawn out, like a country waggon?</ITEM>
<ITEM>Becau&s;e it is tilted.</ITEM>
<ITEM><PB N="88" REF="88">
32 Why is a good cook like a woman of fa|&s;hion?</ITEM>
<ITEM>Becau&s;e &s;he dre&s;&s;es well.</ITEM>
<ITEM>33 Why is a woman's tongue like a good clock?</ITEM>
<ITEM>Becau&s;e it never &s;tands &s;till.</ITEM>
<ITEM>34 Why is a watchmaker like a gardener?</ITEM>
